History.Travels Across Icewind Dale:
At the time when the [[Everlasting Rime]] afflicted the North, in the {{YearlinkName|1489}}, Saarvin could be found traveling the bleak landscape of Icewind Dale. It was during one of his treks that he encountered the [[Uthgardt]] barbarian Runa and an outlander named [[Amos]] unsuccessfully battling a [[remorhaz]].{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 1|9-11}} After Saarvin saved the travelers' lives, the trio returned to the [[Ten Towns]] and met with the druid Belvyre and his bodyguard [[Patience]]. The group vowed to work together to find an [[Ythryn|ancient ruined city]] that held powerful magic that could help Belvyre grow enough croups to help feed the beleaguered Ten Towns.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 1|17-18}}

During their journey to underground city beneath the [[Reghed Glacier]], the group was attacked by [[frost giant skeleton]]s, and Runa was exposed to a growth of [[chardalyn]] that drove her into a murderous frenzy. Amos used the chaos to abduct Belvyre and steal his ''[[frostbrand]]'' walking staff for himself.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 2|15-20}} Runa meanwhile attempted to slay Saarvin, and was only subdued when fellow members of the [[Blue Bear tribe]] arrived to intervene.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|1-5}} The Uthgardt barbarians were themselves ready to kill Saarvin and Patience. They halted all aggressions however, when Runa snapped came to her senses and agree to carry on with their mission.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|11-15}}

Once they arrived at the glacier, the Saarvin and his two companions delved into an old, seemingly-abandoned mine.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|18-19}} They fought against groups of [[duergar]] loyal to [[Xardorok Sunblight]] ruler of the [[Sunblight (fortress)|Sunblight fortress]]. When confronted with overwhelming odds, the trio received aid from Runa's fellow tribespeople.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|1-6}} While they found Belvyre and Amos within the volcanic depths of the glacier, Saarvin was nearly plunged into its depths by an erupting fissure. Runa managed to grab him just in time, saving his life and honoring her debt.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|10-14}} Reunited together, Saarvin, Runa, Patience, and Belvyre managed to climb to safety, marveling at the bountiful growth cause by the magic released from the depths of the glacier.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|17-19}}
